I wonder <answer>(obj in cr)=obj.value*4+11. I don't know the last sentence 'divide evenly among $13$ people' is a bit strange. I wonder whether defining a new variable obj in cr might help. Maybe a method like crottage('obj') also leads to simpler code. Finally, I wonder whether the script read by me can manage more than $100$ things at a time.</think>
Assistant: Let $n$ be the number of jellybeans that Alex has. Then we know three things:
\begin{align*}
n &\geq 100, \\
n &\equiv 11 \pmod {13} \text{.}
\end{align*}
This means that the first $100$ solutions to $n \equiv 11 \pmod {13}$ are $100, 113, \ldots, 256$ and so the first solution $> 100$ (namely $113$) is the solution that we need.

